# Warning/Allow Root-Cause Cleanup Spec

## Scenario: Rust strict lane targets the real workspace
- Given the repository workflow configuration
- When the Rust warning gate runs
- Then it uses `src/compiler_rust` as its workspace root

## Scenario: Simple strict lane is authoritative
- Given the repository workflow configuration
- When the Simple strict lint lane runs
- Then it executes `--deny-all` over the warning/allow cleanup canaries

## Scenario: Primitive-sort strict Rust baseline compiles
- Given the runtime primitive-sort module
- When strict Rust linting builds test targets
- Then the module exposes the NEON threshold constants referenced by its tests
